                    },
                    "body": "Assign to Matthew.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-29T20:04:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-29T20:04:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15165",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The same functionality may be achieved by using namespaces in the FlashMessenger:\n{code}\n$this->_helper->flashMessenger->setNamespace('error')->addMessage('Error message');\n\n\/\/ or:\n$messenger = $this->_helper->getHelper('flashMessenger');\n$messenger->setNamespace('error');\n$messenger->addMessage('Error message');\n{code}\n\nThis is actually one of the primary purposes of namespacing in the FlashMessenger, as it allows you to selectively determine which messages to propagate and retrieve. Typically, however, you will only have a single namespace per controller, so the appropriate location to set the namespace is in preDispatch() or init(), and then simply set and\/or retrieve the messages.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-06-13T09:34:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-06-13T09:34:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/17800",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What about the possibility to specify the namespace in the addMessage() getMessages() signature ?\n\nSo we could do:\n\n{code}\n$messenger->addMessage('Error message', 'my_namespace');\n\n$messenger->getMessages( 'my_namespace');\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-12-06T03:56:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-12-06T03:56:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30429",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=emanaton",
                        "name": "emanaton",
                        "displayName": "Sean P. O. MacCath-Moran",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Greetings All,\n\nFYI, I've created a PriorityMessenger which I believe addresses the needs being expressed here - please check it out and tell me what you think?\nhttp:\/\/emanaton.com\/code\/php\/zendprioritymessenger\n\nRegards,\n\nSean P. O. MacCath-Moran\nwww.emanaton.com",
